      • preQuestionRequeue

        boolean preQuestionRequeue(String loginname,
                         boolean isOperatorMode,
                         Question question,
                         Answer answer,
                         Subproject teilprojekt,
                         int operatorId,
                         long timestamp)
        There are two cases where the method is called
      • the resubmission by pushing the resubmission-button
      • if the operator refuse the question (Forwarding or resubmission with comment)
Parameters:
loginname - loginname from the operator
isOperatorMode - true if the question is opened in the operatormode false otherwise
question - the current question
answer - the current answer
teilprojekt - the subproject on which the question is requeued
operatorId - id of the operator on whom the question is requeued
timestamp - the reque date
Returns:
boolean true if the question may be assigned to the operator, false otherwise
was:
preFrageWiedervorlage

  • preCreateMultiTopicMail

    boolean preCreateMultiTopicMail(String loginname,
                              boolean isOperatorMode,
                              Question sourceQuestion,
                              Question destinationQuestion)
    This rule will be called on creating a multi topic mail. This happens before the new question has been stored. On returning false, creating the copy will be canceled.
    Parameters:
    loginname - login name from the operator
    isOperatorMode - true if the question is opened in the operator mode false otherwise
    sourceQuestion - source question
    destinationQuestion - destination question
    Returns:
    returns true if a multi topic may be created, false otherwise
